What you need to know:  On Sunday, the church held a ceremony in honour of the founder, Lukas Pkiech, who was killed on April 24, 1952.Pkiech was a significant political leader in colonial times and led the Pokot community against European colonisation that led to the Pokot resistance of the 1950s.West Pokot leaders say many followers of the religious groupsÂ were detained, others died and more went into exile and did not return.